<HEADLINE>
<P>
RULING ON ENGLISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding the Supreme Court's decision to let a lower court ruling on 
English-only in the workplace stand (June 21): 
</P>
<P>
 Three cheers for the highest court in the land. The justices' decision to let 
the lower court's ruling stand struck a blow against cultural separation and 
for English as a common language. Perhaps there is a chance for us to deal with 
the divisive multicultural and separatist movements that have plagued us in 
recent times.  
</P>
<P>
 BARBARA COULSON 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
