<P>
NITTY-GRITTY: INSIDE & OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times-Post News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Buff windows to a shine with a clean blackboard eraser, which, rubbed over a 
dry, clean window, will remove lingering smudges. 
</P>
<P>
 * Remove ballpoint ink stains from fabric with hair spray and a dab of liquid 
dish detergent. Rinse with cold water and launder. 
</P>
<P>
 * Perk up outdoor parties with an assortment of odd tables that gain 
uniformity with floor-length coverings made from old sheets, quilts or fabric 
remnants in complementary colors. 
</P>
<P>
 * Spray poison-ivy plants with a mix of two gallons of soapy water and three 
pounds salt. Repeat a few times until plants die. 
</P>
