<P>
SUDDENLY, WORLD CUP IS THE TALK OF THE TOWN FOR THOSE WHO WRITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Picture the seventh game of the NBA finals decided by a Vernon Maxwell shot 
taken a full four minutes after time had run out in the overtime period. This 
is an analogy to the way injury time is kept in World Cup soccer games. Only 
one person, the referee, knows how much time is left at the end of each period. 
</P>
<P>
 I have enjoyed my introduction to international soccer play, but I don't think 
Pat Riley would appreciate playing a guessing game at the end of each period. 
</P>
<P>
 RICHARD W. ADAMS 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos 
