<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.N. OFFICE HEADS FOR GAZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.N. agency for Palestinian refugees will move its headquarters to the 
Gaza Strip from Vienna by the end of next year, a U.N. statement said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The statement released in Cairo said the move was requested by Palestine 
Liberation Organization leader Yasser Arafat. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.N. Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees employs about 8,000 
Palestinians in Gaza and the West Bank and is implementing projects there worth 
$80 million, UNRWA has said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
