<P>
POLICE SEEKING MISSING GIRL, 6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police continued their search Friday for a 6-year-old girl last seen on 
Thursday while playing with friends near her home in the Hyde Park area of 
South-Central Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 The disappearance of Crystal Tymich prompted the Los Angeles Police Department 
to call a localized tactical alert -- which keeps officers on duty after their 
shifts end -- in the South Bureau late Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 100 officers searched the neighborhood around the 6000 block of 
Bryhurst Avenue without success. The alert was cancelled at 4:30 a.m. Friday, 
but officers on regular duty continued to look for the child. 
</P>
<P>
 Police described the girl as white, about 4 feet tall, weighing 60 pounds, 
with hazel eyes and long blond hair. She was wearing a pink T-shirt, 
flower-print shorts, pink socks and white tennis shoes with a picture of a 
mermaid on them when she disappeared. 
