WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; WHAT, BRAZIL WORRIED? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON HARRIS, Times Rio Bureau 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brazilian novelist Joao Ubaldo in Rio de Janeiro's O Globo: 
</P>
<P>
 "I never thought I'd write this, but I'm a bit afraid of playing against the 
United States. It's obvious that, normally, any Brazilian team not composed 
exclusively of wooden leg players would beat the United States. But the way we 
are playing, under pressure to not lose, I prepare myself for 90 minutes of 
suffering and exasperation, as with the awful game against Sweden." 
</P>
