<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; PELE CAN'T STOP, BUT MARADONA 
CAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Without realizing a live feed was sending his comments to viewers across 
Brazil, Galvao Bueno of Globo television was caught complaining about Pele's 
commentary during Brazil's game against Sweden. 
</P>
<P>
 Viewers heard someone at the station ask Bueno to get Pele to "stop talking so 
much." 
</P>
<P>
 Replied Bueno: "What can I do? He keeps talking. I'd have to kill him to get 
him to stop talking." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 On the other hand, during Diego Maradona's impromptu news conference Thursday 
night in Dallas, two radio reporters from Brazil and Argentina started their 
live broadcasts although others asked them to be quiet. 
</P>
<P>
 Suddenly, Maradona turned and pointed at them: " Callate !" or shut up. 
</P>
<P>
 They did. ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
