<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALSA STARTS SEASON BY LOSING TO COLORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Salsa opened this American Professional Soccer League season the way it 
ended the last one -- with a loss to the Colorado Foxes. 
</P>
<P>
 Colorado's Jeff Hooker scored two minutes into overtime Friday to give the 
Foxes a 2-1 victory over the Salsa at Denver's Mile High Stadium.Colorado won 
the 1993 APSL title with a 3-1 victory over the Salsa at Titan Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The Salsa scored first when Jose Vasquez kicked in a rebound of a shot by 
Arturo Velazco that hit the crossbar in the 14th minute. Eleven minutes later, 
Colorado goalkeeper Jim St. Andre made a save on a penalty kick by the Salsa's 
Paulinho, the '92 APSL most valuable player. 
</P>
<P>
 Colorado's Anthony McGreath scored just before halftime to tie the score. 
</P>
<P>
 The winning goal was set up by Chad Ashton's free kick. Hooker controlled the 
rebound and scored. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first game as coach for Rick Davis, who also is the team's general 
manager. 
</P>
<P>
 "Despite the result, it was a good start to our 1994 season," Davis said. "I'm 
happy about our overall performance, but we still have a lot of work to do." 
</P>
<P>
 The Salsa and the Foxes play at Mile High Stadium again next Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
