<TEXT>
<P>
 AMD's Earnings Up Sharply: Sunnyvale, Calif.-based Advanced Micro Devices, 
boosted by surging sales, reported a 45% rise in second-quarter profit.The 
microprocessor manufacturer earned $93.2 million, or 93 cents per share, in the 
quarter ended June 26. A year ago, it earned $64.4 million, or 65 cents per 
share, in the same period. Revenue was $533.3 million, up 30% from $409.1 
million in the year-ago period. "AMD had another excellent quarter as our 
non-microprocessor business grew and microprocessor sales remained at record 
levels," Richard Previte, president and chief operating officer, said in a 
statement. AMD's stock closed up $1 at $26 on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
