<BYLINE>
<P>
By ABIGAIL GOLDMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are investigating the stabbing death of a 31-year-old Pacoima man whose 
body was found early Friday at a Pacoima motel, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 A manager at Las Palmas Motel who had heard gunshots called police at about 
3:30 a.m., said Detective Frank Bishop of the Los Angeles Police Department's 
Foothill Division. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers responding to the scene discovered the body of Derick Pinks, who had 
been stabbed "more than once" in the upper torso, Bishop said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses later told police they saw two men speed off in a beige, 
foreign-made pickup truck just after they heard gunshots, Bishop said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bishop said no motive has been established. Police are looking for the man who 
rented the motel room where Pinks was found. ABIGAIL GOLDMAN 
