<TEXT>
<P>
 Ireland Coach Jack Charlton, who was suspended from his team's game against 
Norway because of "ungentlemanly conduct" in the previous game, is still 
unapologetic over his actions. 
</P>
<P>
 "I still don't know what I did," said Charlton, who grabbed the coat lapels of 
a FIFA official who tried to prevent him from sending two substitutes onto the 
field before the official recorded their arrivals. "But rules are rules. There 
are so many, you don't know which ones you're breaking." HELENE ELLIOTT 
