<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; BRAZIL-USA: HOW HOT IS IT? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is what has happened in this country. A soccer game is a hotter ticket 
than a Grateful Dead concert in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
 That's what they're saying about Monday's second-round game between the United 
State and Brazil at Stanford Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's really off the wall. We're being flooded with phone calls for tickets," 
said Jim Brzowski, vice president of Mr. Ticket, which advertises itself as San 
Francisco's largest ticket broker. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're so busy that we're putting other things like tickets to see the 
Grateful Dead to one side and aren't concerned about any losses on that," he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 David Green of the Best Seat ticket agency in nearby Lafayette went even 
further. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's the biggest sporting event we've ever seen. Bigger than the Super Bowl, 
bigger than the World Series," he said. 
</P>
