<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; JOURNALISTS AREN'T 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times news services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 By an overwhelming margin, the 2,310 journalists who participated in an Adidas 
survey selected Brazil to win the World Cup. 
</P>
<P>
 In voting done before June 26, nearly 70% of the journalists felt Brazil would 
reach the final, and of those, 80% predicted that the Brazilians would win. The 
runner-up was Germany, with 1,115 votes as a participant in the finals and 420 
to finish as champion. Argentina and Italy finished third and fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty-one journalists picked the United States to win the Cup. 
</P>
