</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four men suspected of forcing their way into a 26-year-old woman's apartment 
were being held Friday on suspicion of robbery and rape, police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors saw four men with guns entering the woman's apartment in the 1100 
block of Mayfair Avenue about 3:45 p.m. Thursday and called police, Lt. Vince 
Howard said. 
</P>
<P>
 When officers arrived, the woman and her 6-year-old daughter were attempting 
to get out but one of the gunmen pulled them back into the apartment. A short 
time later, the woman and child were allowed to leave the apartment. The woman 
told police she had been raped. The child was not harmed, Howard said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers ordered the men out of the apartment and three of them complied. They 
were immediately taken into custody. A fourth man stayed inside for 40 minutes 
before surrendering without incident. Police recovered four guns at the scene, 
Howard said. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrested were: Antonio Julian Valdez, 19, and Ray Nel Ramos, 22, both of 
Anaheim, and Douglas Joel Audette and Juan Pablo Camacho both 18 and from Buena 
Park. All were being held at Anaheim city jail. GREG HERNANDEZ 
