<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. RELIGION NOTES / DAYE CLARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAYE CLARK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Temple Isaiah of Newport Beach announced that Cantor Vladimir Shtayerman has 
joined the staff.He is from Moscow, where he attended the Moscow Academy of 
Jewish Arts. An accomplished concert soloist, he has given concerts in the 
Moscow Conservatory Hall, singing with the Georgian Philarmony. 
</P>
<P>
 He can be heard on Fridays at 8 p.m. during the services led by Rabbi Marc 
Rubenstein. The synagogue is at 2401 Irvine Ave. Information: (714) 548-6900. 
</P>
</TEXT>
